'''LatencyTOP''' is a [[Linux]] [[Application software|application]] for identifying [[operating system]] [[Latency (engineering)|latency]] within the [[Kernel (computing)|kernel]] and find out the operations/actions which cause the latency. LatencyTOP is a tool for [[software developers]] to visualize system latencies. Based on these observations, the [[source code]] of the application or kernel can be modified to reduce latency. It was released by [[Intel]] in 2008 under the [[GNU General Public License|GPL]]v2 license. It works for [[Intel]], [[Advanced Micro Devices|AMD]] and [[ARM architecture|ARM]] [[processors]].{{Citation needed|date=November 2010}}
The project appears to be dead as the website is gone and there have not been commits since 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ohloh.net/p/latencytop|title=The LatencyTOP Open Source Project on Open Hub|publisher=}}</ref>
